This paper discusses the limitations of LoRaWAN technology in the context of IoT applications, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the communication protocols and signal processing techniques used in LoRaWAN, which could fall under information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the need for understanding the limitations of LoRaWAN in order to avoid security risks, which could fall under cyber security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper provides use case examples, which could fall under machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.MA) as these technologies are often used in IoT applications.
